What is a hash?
A hash in a collection of different keys and their values

What are some examples of information that would be Hashes as opposed to some other data type?
an example could be like different breeds of dogs.  Bulldog, Boxer, lab etc...

How are Hashes and Arrays similar? How are they different?
They both store a collection of different objects but arrays use integers as its index but a hash lets you use any object type

How do you retrieve a particular value from a Hash?
student = {name = Peter, eye color = green}
student =["eye color"]  should return green

How do you add information to a Hash?
you can add it similar to an array but have to use {}. first you name the hash then assign the value to the key

How would you perform an operation on every element inside a Hash?
need to come back to

How would you change the value of a particular element in a Hash?
To change it I would reference the initial entry and then set it to the new info.

How do you delete an element from a Hash?
You use the delete function.  referencing the student one adn eye color from earlier an example would be
my.hash.delete "Pete"

What happens if you try to retrieve an element from a Hash that does not exist in the Hash?
you get a nil response because it simply does not exisit

How do you determine how many elements are in a Hash?
through the length function
